        "sha": "a944aaf2a620dc1699c459fedea0631bb2b4e00b",
        "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/bitcoin/bitcoin/git/trees/a944aaf2a620dc1699c459fedea0631bb2b4e00b"
      },
      "verification": {
        "verified": true,
        "reason": "valid",
        "payload": "tree a944aaf2a620dc1699c459fedea0631bb2b4e00b\nparent ea9afb61a1c52979d0e64e4dae9b3a611f7b9a5e\nauthor Matthew Zipkin <pinheadmz@pm.me> 1782505994 -0400\ncommitter Matthew Zipkin <pinheadmz@pm.me> 1782563243 -0400\n\nhttp: prevent race condition between worker thread and I/O thread\n\nThis prevents a losing race condition that could prevent the server\nfrom reading requests from an HTTP client.\n\nA connected socket can either be written to or read from based on the\nresult of GenerateWaitSockets(). That method checks the HTTPRemoteClient\nflag m_send_ready. If it's `true` the implication is that there is\ndata in the client's send buffer ready to go. Once that data is sent\nand the buffer is empty, MaybeSendBytesFromBuffer() sets it `false` again.\n\nThe sad case was when a worker thread calling WriteReply() adds\ndata to the send buffer, but before it sets m_send_ready to `true`,\nthe I/O thread sends that data and empties the buffer. With the\nbuffer unexpectedly empty, WriteReply() sets m_send_ready to `true`.\n\nThe effect of this is that the socket will stay in \"write\" mode\nwith nothing to write. With nothing to write, MaybeSendBytesFromBuffer()\nnever sets it back to `false` and the socket is stuck forever.\n",
        "signature": "-----BEGIN PGP SIGNATURE-----\n\niQJPBAABCAA5FiEE5hdzzW4BBA4vG9eM5+KYS2KJyToFAmo/wasbFIAAAAAABAAO\nbWFudTIsMi41KzEuMTIsMCwzAAoJEOfimEtiick6DwcP/3ppY/5veVhZvtJ6IS5y\nlqHt9Wjm4xX0J89a7OQvcjFqXT3TxBFAM98XnN+Vcj6e46+U3jLckUt9zcD7Fnyk\noKJcNkG0lVDZu+2QzG7lGak/+yUt2PTdikpRfxoJOV+53736MHA2hVMPGmTczDdN\nzwAHfwBfvThwBp647h0wFyDx3plhN2vwKEAORGHGcX2xgQzdl1RITrMmPm/q8ffW\nSfe7UlO1JpFVnwXPIvKe1unUDifZCFTQA6TRpLPm4leELbe9r0DO2mwXJ3TYLBmO\nMzjHbnaopnGW8aQtRFzatg/IaDt1eYzzymzApoQZOhj9/x/pz2he6Sq9ont0OQsA\nuKQn0U3/hvq/gYRW9jRBUIo1yR8TlP5pxEH7ab0GkeZxx5OAoGcn+PVRFONGPMCr\nAVMv7MXIuPaqsjov1JUy/nF6D7xGgPonIV+7D1Gk+oVm5steHuqzwgr1X+NwJ18j\nViNgW1u68OhnDeuBRKNDD8njkUV2fY4O2KDMjMZe2wX2aonQIwnYiVoyC5+x275H\nLoylm+ZwB9SbQ17UG8gMarlfJY3JlMJcr9gKJ9weZaLJM/XnPyBy+diZHtaRbCBH\njUIrYagh18/eOf5HN0VVQKDlBJ/R045wmzMImyte3JM8V5vstPBAd/8h1vt9+812\nJ/zLlZfTemsSEotE5sUJJQKk\n=a1rY\n-----END PGP SIGNATURE-----"
